Diagnosis. Opercular verticil with 13–15 spines equal in size (no larger dorsal spine) curved outward, with pointed tips, each verticil spine with 4–6 pairs of lateral spinules directed obliquely outwards. All verticil spines also with 4–6 accessory teeth arranged in a single row on inner side. Central tooth longer than verticil spines, may be smooth, but mostly bearing numerous randomly placed small teeth distally. Funnel not chitinized, with 15–20 blunt-tipped radii. Grooves separating radii extending 1 / 3 of funnel length (
Fig. 6
).
